<subSubSection id="24DC108B5E66C529FF3FBB0FFC33E93C" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="6C7943005E66C529FF3FBB0FFC33E93C" blockId="100.[151,1436,151,1112]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E66C529FF3FBB0FFE90E95F" bold="true" box="[199,326,1052,1076]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Etymology</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E66C529FEA2BB0FFE05E95F" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" box="[346,467,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Poluninius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E66C529FEA2BB0FFE05E95F" box="[346,467,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Poluninius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(masculine) is a noun latinised from the surname of the late Ivan Polunin who collected the few species of this unusual genus, and is named in his honour.
</paragraph>
